{
  "stem": "2460.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were only two, maybe three Jewish families in the entire street where we lived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had very good relationships with the Gentile population.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, very well.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, some of them were very good friends, yes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, only doing the Hungarian occupation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not in the Slovak or Czechoslovakian occupation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what I remember is that one day, my mother and my father told us that the Hungarians are occupying our city.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother was born in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she was waiting for the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in the morning, the day the Czechoslovakian army moved out from our city, and they throw garbage all over with their tanks to disturb the Hungarian army to parade into our city, Levice.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we-- we liked the Czechoslovakian army.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were-- we couldn't believe that they are moving out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But of course, as a little boy, so we waiting it for some-- for the changes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So the Hungarians came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- I think it was November-- end of November 1938.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was seven years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when the Hungarian army came into the town, it was a terrible disappointment.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They looked differently than the-- than the Czechoslovakian army.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were very poorly dressed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the main thing is they were singing anti-Jewish [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] slogans and anti-Jewish songs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So it was a terrible disappointment to the Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, of course, because we spoke Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just dirty Jews, you are going to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And we couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a drastic change.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At night, a bus came to our city, a huge bus.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember the bus because I never saw such a big bus before.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Those were the Hungarian-- the representatives of the Hungarian government.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
